<subSubSection id="C3406577FFC3FA33FF72FAFCFE816F8C" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE536FCFFC3FA3EFF72FAFCFCF26F95" blockId="7.[192,803,948,1890]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFF72FAFCFE986F1F" bold="true" box="[240,353,1285,1308]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Remarks:</emphasis>
the adult specimens were collected among rocks and rotten logs during a night search with UV light (02:30 hrs), in an area which had been cleared for building purposes at an altitude of 
<quantity id="4CA29B19FFC3FA3EFDEFFA98FD4D6F7B" box="[621,692,1377,1400]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
a.s.l. The juvenile was found among bracts of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFDC6FA86FD546F95" box="[580,685,1407,1430]" class="Liliopsida" family="Heliconiaceae" genus="Heliconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zingiberales" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFDC6FA86FD546F95" box="[580,685,1407,1430]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Heliconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE536FCFFC3FA3EFF72FA67FB3A6E25" blockId="7.[192,803,948,1890]" lastBlockId="7.[830,1442,948,1890]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
In a previous paper, Teruel &amp; García (2008b: 10– 12) commented on the deep taxonomic problems of the Colombian members of the “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFD82FA22FD4E6FF1" box="[512,695,1499,1522]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clathratus">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFD82FA22FD4E6FF1" box="[512,695,1499,1522]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Tityus clathratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” speciesgroup, and made a special reference to inadequate or unreliable diagnoses of most species, including 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFD5AF9E0FF0B6C4D" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFD5AF9E0FF0B6C4D" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFEABF9CEFE736C4D" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[297,394,1591,1614]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFEABF9CEFE736C4D" box="[297,394,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additional specimens studied herein allow updating and correcting the diagnosis of the former according to the current taxonomy of this group. It is worth to note here that the presence of a smooth patch in sternite V is now confirmed for both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFC8FF94BFEEA6CEB" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFC8FF94BFEEA6CEB" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as previously suggested by Teruel &amp; García (2008: 12). This patch is small and flat in the adult male (
<figureCitation id="13612A79FFC3FA3EFF4AF8F7FEE26D26" box="[200,283,1806,1829]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[192,268,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[191,1441,215,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-10@6.[192,1440,216,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4: Adult male of Tityus tayrona from Turbaco: a) carapace; b) pedipalp, dorsal view; c) sternopectinal region; d) sternite V; e) metasomal segments I–III, lateral view; f) metasomal segments IV–V and telson, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4649091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4649091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
), and even less conspicuous in adult female (
<figureCitation id="13612A79FFC3FA3EFF45F8D4FEE36D47" box="[199,282,1837,1860]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[192,268,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[191,1441,215,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[192,1440,216,1800]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6: Adult female of Tityus tayrona from Turbaco: a) carapace; b) pedipalp, dorsal view; c) sternopectinal region; d) sternite V; e) metasomal segments I–III, lateral view; f) metasomal segments IV–V and telson, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4649095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4649095/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 6d</figureCitation>
); thus, it is obvious that it was simply overlooked by these authors in their specimens; this is even demonstrated in the paper by Botero-Trujillo &amp; Fagua (2007), where this patch is explicitly stated to be absent in text page 133, but is in turn clearly shown in the figures 13 and 15 of the same paper.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE536FCFFC3FA30FCECFBD7FE1D6D0E" blockId="7.[830,1442,948,1890]" lastBlockId="9.[192,803,1568,1897]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
On the other hand, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFBCBFBD7FB216E46" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[1097,1240,1070,1093]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFBCBFBD7FB216E46" box="[1097,1240,1070,1093]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Tityus erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Lourenço (1999) on the basis of a single juvenile male, and it was originally separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFB5FFB92FAA96E81" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[1245,1360,1131,1154]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFB5FFB92FAA96E81" box="[1245,1360,1131,1154]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of only three supposedly diagnostic characters: “... 
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFCBCFB50FAF86EDD" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">a more intense and darker pigmentation generally, a greater distance between median eyes,</emphasis>
[...] 
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFAC5FB3EFB696F1F" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">and the presence of a smooth and shining expanded zone on the posterior region of sternite V</emphasis>
...” (Lourenço, 1999: 2; italics herein added). Juvenile 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFB08FADAFB336F39" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[1162,1226,1315,1338]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFB08FADAFB336F39" box="[1162,1226,1315,1338]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Tityus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have no taxonomic value at all, because they lack secondary sexual dimorphism which is critical to diagnose closely related species, and this fact alone renders both Lourenço’s diagnosis and selection of the 
<typeStatus id="54E1885EFFC3FA3EFB2BFA67FAFF6FB6" box="[1193,1286,1438,1461]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFABBFA67FA586FB6" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[1337,1441,1438,1461]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFABBFA67FA586FB6" box="[1337,1441,1438,1461]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
useless. Apart from this, the first two characters used by Lourenço are largely known to vary from juvenile through adult instars in all species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFB76FA03FACC6C12" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[1268,1333,1530,1553]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFB76FA03FACC6C12" box="[1268,1333,1530,1553]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Tityus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and thus cannot be used as diagnostic, so we are only left with character 3 to separate 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFBC7F9CEFB516C4D" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[1093,1192,1591,1614]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFBC7F9CEFB516C4D" box="[1093,1192,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFB70F9CEFA9C6C4D" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[1266,1381,1591,1614]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFB70F9CEFA9C6C4D" box="[1266,1381,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The examination of the additional specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFAAEF9AFFA596C6E" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[1324,1440,1622,1645]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFAAEF9AFFA596C6E" box="[1324,1440,1622,1645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
herein recorded (which are all clearly conspecific) confirmed that the smooth patch of sternite V is also present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFC42F94BFBC16CCA" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[960,1080,1714,1737]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFC42F94BFBC16CCA" box="[960,1080,1714,1737]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that it is ontogenetically variable: in males it is expanded and bulky in the juvenile instars (see our 
<figureCitation id="13612A79FFC3FA3EFBC0F916FB6F6D05" box="[1090,1174,1775,1798]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="9.[192,268,1492,1515]" captionTargetBox="[191,1440,191,1462]" captionTargetId="figure-6@9.[192,1439,192,1461]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 7: Juvenile male of Tityus tayrona from Turbaco: a) entire dorsal view; b) entire ventral view; c) sternite V." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4649097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4649097/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 7c</figureCitation>
, which shows a patch identical to that depicted in Lourenço [1999: fig. 6] for the 
<typeStatus id="54E1885EFFC3FA3EFCE5F8D4FC3C6D47" box="[871,965,1837,1860]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFC3FA3EFC6FF8D4FBB26D47" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[1005,1099,1837,1860]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFC3FA3EFC6FF8D4FBB26D47" box="[1005,1099,1837,1860]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and it becomes much smaller and flat in the adult instar (see our 
<figureCitation id="13612A79FFC3FA3EFB6AF8B2FAC46D61" box="[1256,1341,1867,1890]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[192,268,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[191,1441,215,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-10@6.[192,1440,216,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4: Adult male of Tityus tayrona from Turbaco: a) carapace; b) pedipalp, dorsal view; c) sternopectinal region; d) sternite V; e) metasomal segments I–III, lateral view; f) metasomal segments IV–V and telson, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4649091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4649091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Figs. 4d</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="13612A79FFC3FA3EFAF0F8B2FA696D61" box="[1394,1424,1867,1890]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[192,268,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[191,1441,215,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[192,1440,216,1800]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6: Adult female of Tityus tayrona from Turbaco: a) carapace; b) pedipalp, dorsal view; c) sternopectinal region; d) sternite V; e) metasomal segments I–III, lateral view; f) metasomal segments IV–V and telson, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4649095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4649095/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">6d</figureCitation>
). Apart from this, the juvenile male 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFCDFA30FDD1F9D9FD316C34" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[595,712,1568,1591]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFCDFA30FDD1F9D9FD316C34" box="[595,712,1568,1591]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
studied herein matches every point of the original description and figures of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFCDFA30FEE4F9A4FE306C77" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" box="[358,457,1629,1652]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFCDFA30FEE4F9A4FE306C77" box="[358,457,1629,1652]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">T. erikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exactly and the distribution of both taxa is also coincident, demonstrating that the 
<typeStatus id="54E1885EFFCDFA30FF42F963FEE76CB2" box="[192,286,1690,1713]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
of the latter is merely a juvenile 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFCDFA30FD25F963FCE26CB2" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[679,795,1690,1713]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFCDFA30FD25F963FCE26CB2" box="[679,795,1690,1713]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">T. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, the following synonymy is herein established: 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFCDFA30FF42F92EFDE46CED" authority="Lourenco, 1991" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1991" box="[192,541,1751,1774]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFCDFA30FF42F92EFE986CED" box="[192,353,1751,1774]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Tityus tayrona</emphasis>
Lourenço, 1991
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7FFFCDFA30FDC5F92EFEC16D0E" authority="Lourenco, 1999" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1999" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erikae" status="new synonym">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFCDFA30FDC5F92EFD216CED" box="[583,728,1751,1774]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Tityus erikae</emphasis>
Lourenço, 1999
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B92EEAEEFFCDFA30FEC0F90FFE246D0E" bold="true" box="[322,477,1782,1805]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21D5795FFCDFA30FEC0F90FFE246D0E" box="[322,477,1782,1805]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">new synonym</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
